<div class="modal fade" id="placement-help-modal" tabindex="-1">
    <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title">Placement phase</h5>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <h6>When is it?</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small">The placement phase runs for a limited time — exact dates will be shown here soon. Place your barrio before it closes!</p>

                <h6>Placing your barrio</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small">Click <strong>Add my barrio on the map</strong> to start drawing. Then click on the map to drop points that define your space — each click adds a corner. Close the shape by clicking back on the first point.</p>
                <div class="bg-light border rounded mb-3 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="height:100px">
                    <span class="text-muted small fst-italic">Screenshot coming soon</span>
                </div>

                <h6>Adjusting the shape</h6>
                <ul class="text-muted small ps-3 mb-2">
                    <li>Drag a corner point to move it</li>
                    <li>Drag the whole shape to reposition it</li>
                    <li>Click the midpoint of an edge (where the length in metres is shown) to add a new corner</li>
                    <li>Click a point to select it (it turns orange), then press <kbd>Delete</kbd> or <kbd>Backspace</kbd> to remove it</li>
                    <li>The area in m² is shown in the centre and updates as you edit</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="bg-light border rounded mb-3 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="height:100px">
                    <span class="text-muted small fst-italic">Screenshot coming soon</span>
                </div>

                <h6>Saving &amp; editing later</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small">Happy with it? Hit <strong>Save</strong>. Afterwards, click your barrio on the map to see its size, then <strong>Edit</strong> to jump back into edit mode. Every save creates a history entry — use the <strong>History</strong> button to browse and restore any previous version. No stress, you can't break anything!</p>

                <h6>Colours &amp; sound zones</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small">Each barrio is coloured by its preferred sound zone (editable from your barrio page). Not sure which zone fits? Have a look at the map and chat with your neighbours!</p>

                <h6>Stay inside the white zones</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small">The dashed white areas mark the safe camping zones, protected by lightning poles. <strong>Camping outside them is not allowed</strong>, so keep your barrio inside those boundaries.</p>

                <h6>Overlaps? Talk it out!</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small">If your barrio overlaps with another, reach out on <a href="https://discord.com/channels/1462886445583962245/1467793922074873896" target="_blank" class="text-decoration-none">Discord #city-planning</a> and work it out together. If there are unresolved conflicts at the end of the phase, the city planning team will sort them out.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
